                            Installation instruction
                            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. FreeBSD
~~~~~~~~~~
a. From binary (txz) package

   Use package manager to install/remove application.

b. From source package

   Build and install:
   # tar -xzf c3-0.6.tar.gz
   # ./configure
   # make
   # make install

   Remove:
   # make uninstall

2. Linux
~~~~~~~~
a. From binary (deb, package, rpm, txz) package

   Use package manager to install/remove application.

b. From binary (bin) package

   Install:
   # ./c3-0.6-i586.bin

   Remove:
   # /opt/c3/uninstall

c. From binary (tar.gz) package

   Install:
   # cp c3-0.6-i586.tar.gz /opt
   # cd /opt
   # tar -xzf c3-0.6-i586.tar.gz
   # cd c3
   # ./create_links
            or
   # tar -xzf c3-0.6-i586.tar.gz
   # cd c3
   # ./install

   Remove:
   # /opt/c3/remove_links
   # rm -r /opt/c3/
            or
   # /opt/c3/uninstall

d. From source package

   Build and install:
   $ tar -xzf c3-0.6.tar.gz
   $ ./configure
   $ make
   # make install

   Remove:
   # make uninstall

3. Windows
~~~~~~~~~~
a. From binary (exe) package

   Run installer file and follow intructions.

b. From binary (msi) package

   > msiexec.exe /i c3-0.6-win32.msi    (or double-click to open package) 

c. From binary (zip) package

   > unzip c3-0.6-win32.zip             (or use unpacking application)

d. From source package

   Build and install:
   > tar -xzf c3-0.6.tar.gz             (or use unpacking application)
   > build.bat
   > build.bat install

   Remove:
   > build.bat uninstall

